In the LpSolver_CMD class, executable function (line 338):

```
def executable(command):
        """Checks that the solver command is executable,
        And returns the actual path to it."""

        if os.path.isabs(command):
            if os.path.exists(command) and os.access(command, os.X_OK):
                return command
        for path in os.environ.get("PATH", []).split(os.pathsep):
            new_path = os.path.join(path, command)
            if os.path.exists(new_path) and os.access(new_path, os.X_OK):
                return os.path.join(path, command)
        return False
```

I believe the function should either change the value of self.path, or all future references to executable should assign the variable to its return value. Currently, if the executable exists under a different path in os.environ["PATH"], executable(self.path) returns the new path, but GLPK_CMD does not adjust accordingly.

